          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "- By author.  One can see that the cross section",
                "calculated simply from the yields using a constant",
                "multiplier factor at 165 degrees in angular",
                "distribution for 6.576 MeV is about 25 mb/sr, which is",
                "much smaller than the cross section - ~40 mb/sr - at",
                "6.576 MeV in the excitation function at 165 degrees.",
                "This discrepancy can be explained by the resonance",
                "pair at 6.576 MeV with resonant with 40 keV and target",
                "thickness.   In order to get forward-scattering angular",
                "distribution data, glancing incidence was taken.  Thus,",
                "the target is 30 KeV thick, which is larger than the",
                "value 12 keV in normal incidence."
              ]
            }
          ],
